1. cat /proc/sys/kernel/threads-max  :- this command will give the max no of threads ongoing
this max no of threads ongoing is stored in file thread-max

2. sudo su :- this cmd allows you to run  a command as root user
3.type password
4. cmd:- " echo 7000 > /proc/sys/kernel/threads-max ":- this will set 7000 as the max thread. ( > is redirector operator ),
5. cat /proc/sys/kernel/threads-max :- now thread-max value will be 7000

cat is used for listing content of some file
echo is used for listing value of some variable
